  "prompt": "What's a good opening line for a psychology personal statement that has a lasting effect and stands out?",
  "response": "Crafting a compelling opening line for your psychology personal statement is crucial for capturing the admissions committee's attention. Consider starting with a vivid anecdote or intriguing fact that reflects your unique perspective or passion for psychology. Here's an example:\n\n\"Watching my younger brother navigate the world with autism taught me that the mind's complexities are not just subjects to study, but puzzles to piece together with empathy and insight.\"\n\nThis line uses a personal story to highlight your motivation and a deeper understanding, setting the stage for a memorable and engaging personal statement.",
